 \lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} \ \frac{n}{n \ \sqrt{n^2 + 1}} \ = \ \lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} \ \frac{1}{ \ \sqrt{n^2 + 1}} \ = \ 0 \ ,  
