\frac{1}{n\sqrt{n^2+1}}<\frac{1}{n^2}
n\sqrt{n^2+1}>n^2$$ \forall n\in \mathbb{N}
 \int_1^\infty \frac{dx}{x \sqrt{x^2+1}}  = \left. \ln \frac{x}{1 + \sqrt{1 + x^2}} \right|_1^\infty  = 1 - \frac{1}{1 + \sqrt{2}} < \infty 
\sim \frac{1}{n^2}
